NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
HOST=0.0.0.0

# Database (Required)
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=healthcare_coordination
DB_USER=healthcare_app
DB_PASSWORD=<CHANGE_ME_STRONG_PASSWORD>
DB_SSL=true
DB_MAX_CONNECTIONS=20

# Redis (Required)
REDIS_HOST=localhost
REDIS_PORT=6379
REDIS_PASSWORD=<CHANGE_ME_STRONG_PASSWORD>
REDIS_TLS=true

# JWT (Required - Min 256 bits)
JWT_SECRET=<CHANGE_ME_MINIMUM_64_CHAR_CRYPTOGRAPHICALLY_RANDOM_SECRET>
JWT_EXPIRY=3600

# API Keys (Required - Min 256 bits)
API_KEY_SECRET=<CHANGE_ME_MINIMUM_64_CHAR_CRYPTOGRAPHICALLY_RANDOM_SECRET>

# CORS (Required - No wildcards)
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://example.com,https://app.example.com

# Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100

# EHR Integration
EHR_FHIR_BASE_URL=https://ehr-system.example.com/fhir
EHR_CLIENT_ID=<YOUR_EHR_CLIENT_ID>
EHR_CLIENT_SECRET=<YOUR_EHR_CLIENT_SECRET>

# Encryption (Required - 32 bytes hex)
ENCRYPTION_KEY=<CHANGE_ME_64_CHAR_HEX_STRING>

# ============================================================================
// README.md
// ============================================================================
# Healthcare Coordination System

Production-ready healthcare coordination platform with comprehensive security controls.

## Features
- Patient intake: registration, demographics, consent management, structured intake workflows
- EHR integrations: HL7/FHIR R4-compliant APIs, bidirectional sync, configurable adapters
- Referral management: create/receive referrals, status tracking, specialist assignment
- Multi-provider scheduling: calendar management, appointment slots, conflict resolution, reminders
- Billing: claims submission, real-time eligibility verification, EOB processing, payment posting
- Clinical reporting: quality metrics dashboards, regulatory reports, PDF/CSV export

## Architecture
- Layered design: API → Service → Domain → Persistence
- PostgreSQL for ACID-compliant data storage with PHI encryption at rest
- Redis for rate limiting, session management, and caching
- OpenAPI 3.0 specification included
- Structured audit logging for all state changes

## Security Controls (Enforced by Default)
- Mandatory authentication on all endpoints (except /health)
- Per-client rate limiting with Redis-backed state
- JWT with algorithm enforcement (HS256), exp/iat validation
- Explicit CORS origins (no wildcards)
- Request size limits (10MB), pagination limits (max 100/page, max offset 10000)
- Constant-time secret comparison
- PHI encryption at rest (AES-256-GCM)
- Comprehensive input validation (Joi schemas)
- Generic error responses (no internal leakage)
- Startup validation: all secrets, DB, Redis verified before accepting traffic

## Prerequisites
- Node.js ≥18.0.0
- PostgreSQL ≥14
- Redis ≥7

## Installation

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env
# EDIT .env with production values - ALL secrets are REQUIRED
npm run build
npm run migrate
npm start
```

## Database Migrations

Migrations auto-run on startup. Manual execution:
```bash
npm run migrate
```

## API Documentation

OpenAPI spec: `/api/docs` (authenticated)

Health check: `GET /health` (unauthenticated)

## Environment Variables

All variables in .env.example are REQUIRED. System fails fast if:
- Any required variable is missing or empty
- JWT_SECRET or API_KEY_SECRET < 64 characters
- ENCRYPTION_KEY is not 64-char hex
- CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS contains wildcards or is empty
- Database/Redis connection fails

## Compliance

- HIPAA: PHI encrypted at rest and in transit, audit logs for all access
- FHIR R4: Full support for Patient, Encounter, Observation, Claim resources
- HL7 v2: Parser included for ADT, ORM, ORU message types

